So as a child growing up in a

35:50.716 --> 35:53.784
home of addiction, I didn't

35:53.785 --> 35:55.253
understand how they could do all

35:55.254 --> 35:57.087
the stuff that they did to me

35:57.088 --> 35:58.289
and my brother and sister.

35:58.290 --> 35:59.724
Like don't you love me enough?

35:59.725 --> 36:01.892
Then I became a mother, and then

36:01.893 --> 36:03.594
I became a heroin addict.

36:03.595 --> 36:09.467
And I did all that
stuff to my kids.

36:09.468 --> 36:10.369
My doctor was my
biggest drug dealer.

36:10.370 --> 36:12.737
Married, had a baby, fell
down the stairs, two jobs,

36:12.738 --> 36:14.038
college on top of it.

36:14.039 --> 36:15.440
Next thing I know I'm on the

36:15.441 --> 36:17.242
prescriptions, that's where
